e, G., Schleser, G.H., Dehairs, F., Beeckman, H., Koedam, N., Annual cyclicity in high-resolution stable carbon and oxygen isotope ratios in the wood of the mangrove tree Rhizophora mucronata (2004) Plant, Cell and Environment, 27 (12), pp. 1525-1536. , DOI 10.1111/j.1365-3040.2004.01258.x; Verheyden, A., Annual cyclicity in high-resolution stable carbon and oxygen isotope ratios in the wood of the mangrove tree Rhizophora mucronata (2004) Plant Cell Environ, 27, pp. 1525-1536. , (Pubitemid 39623420); Evans, M.N., Toward forward modeling for paleoclimatic proxy signal calibration: A case study with oxygen isotopic composition of tropical woods (2007) Geochem Geophy Geosy, 8, pp. Q07008; Evans, M.N., A reactor for high temperature pyrolysis and oxygen isotopic analysis of cellulose via induction heating (2008) Rapid Comm Mass Sp, 22, pp. 2211-2219; Barbour, M.M., Roden, J.S., Farquhar, G.D., Ehleringer, J.R., Expressing leaf water and cellulose oxygen isotope ratios as enrichment above source water reveals evidence of a Peclet effect (2004) Oecologia, 138, pp. 426-435; Kaplan, A., Analyses of global sea surface temperature 1856-1991 (1998) J Geophys Res, 103, pp. 18567-18589; Kalnay, E., The NCEP/NCAR 40-year reanalysis project (1996) B Am Meteorol Soc, 77, pp. 437-471; Enfield, D.B., Lee, S.K., Wang, C., How are large Western Hemisphere warm pools formed? (2006) Prog Oceanogr, 70, pp. 346-365; Fleming, T., Secular changes in Costa Rican rainfall: Correlation with elevation (1986) J Trop Ecol, 2, pp. 87-91; Peterson, T.C., Vose, R.S., An Overview of the Global Historical Climatology Network Temperature Database (1997) Bulletin of the American Meteorological Society, 78 (12), pp. 2837-2849; Peterson, T.C., Vose, R.S., An overview of the Global Historical Climatology Network temperature database (1997) B Am Meteorol Soc, 78, pp. 2837-2849. , (Pubitemid 127483239); Rhodes, A.L., Guswa, A.J., Newell, S.E., Seasonal variation in the stable isotopic composition of precipit